<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}+{4}{y}={44}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{x}-{2}{y}=-{14}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{4},{9}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}+{4}{y}={44}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}={44}-{\left({4}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{44}-{\left({4}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{2}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{\left(\frac{{{44}-{\left({4}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{2}}}}\right)}+-{2}{y}=-{14}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{1}}{{-{{2}}}}\cdot{\left({44}\right)}--\frac{{1}}{{-{{2}}}}{\left({4}\right)}{y}+-{2}{y}=-{14}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{22}-{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}+-{2}{y}=-{14}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{y}+{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}=-{14}-{22}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{y}+{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}=-{36}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{2}+{\left(-{2}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{36}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{y}=-{36}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{36}}{{-{{4}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={9}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}+{4}{\left({9}\right)}={44}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}+{\left({36}\right)}={44}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}={44}-{\left({36}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{8}}{{-{{2}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{4}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{4},{9}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

